      <div xml:id="Aink3-kilavi">
        <p type="edition"> ituvumatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="Aink3">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> pālpala vūṟuka pakaṭupala ciṟakka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> vittiya vuḻavar nelloṭu peyarum</l>
          <l> pūkkaña lūraṉ ṟaṉmaṉai </l>
          <l> vāḻkkai polika veṉavēṭ ṭēmē. </l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

<l>          'Long live Ātan! Long live Aviṉi! </l>
<l>          May many [drops of] milk flow! May many bulls grow!' </l>
<l>          That's what your mother wanted. As for me: </l>
<l>          '[There is] a man from a land filled with flowers,</l>
<l>          where ploughmen, after sowing, return with paddy:</l>
<l>          May the life of his house flourish!' — that's what I wanted. </l>
          


        </lg>
      </div>
